  "text": "The rapid time course of recovery of Fv/Fm immediately following high PFD treatment (Figs. 6, 7, and 8) is suggestive of the relaxation of a fluorescence quenching component related to thylakoid membrane energization [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The diminishing amplitude of this rapidly relaxing component in resistant discs (Figs. 6, 7 , and 8) suggests that the mechanism that causes the relaxation was rendered inactive by high PFD exposure. Again, clarification of the nature of this component will require additional experimentation.",
